Package cornflakes.lang

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ArrayIterator
    The ArrayIterator class is used internally in for-each loops to create an iterator object to iterate over an array.
    BoolPointer
    The BoolPointer class is the wrapper type for the bool* Cornflakes type.
    CharPointer
    The CharPointer class is the wrapper type for the char* Cornflakes type.
    F32Pointer
    The F32Pointer class is the wrapper type for the f32* Cornflakes type.
    F32Range
    The F32Range class is an iterable Range implementation used for defining a range between two floating-point values, including an optional increment size.
    F64Pointer
    The F64Pointer class is the wrapper type for the f64* Cornflakes type.
    FunctionalIterator<T>
    The FunctionalIterator class is an iterator implementation which has several convenience functions commonly found in other languages.
    I16Pointer
    The I16Pointer class is the wrapper type for the i16* Cornflakes type.
    I32Pointer
    The I32Pointer class is the wrapper type for the i32* Cornflakes type.
    I32Range
    The I32Range class is an iterable Range implementation used for defining a range between two integer values, including an optional increment size.
    I64Pointer
    The I64Pointer class is the wrapper type for the i64* Cornflakes type.
    I8Pointer
    The I8Pointer class is the wrapper type for the i8* Cornflakes type.
    Main
    A temporary class for testing Cornflakes stuff that I often accidentally check into the repo because I'm in a hurry.
    ObjectPointer
    The ObjectPointer class is the wrapper type for any Cornflakes non-primtive pointer type.
    Pointer
    The Pointer class is the superclass type for all Cornflakes pointer wrapper classes.
    Range
    The Range class represents any given range between two primitive values.
    StringUtility
    Internally used by the compiler to append strings to other strings and other types.
    Tuple
    The wrapper class for any Cornflakes tuple.
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    IteratorException
    An IteratorException is an unchecked exception thrown when an invalid operation is performed on a FunctionalIterator.
